						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the west wall of the front <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the Vēṇugōpālasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1763 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Refers to the service (to the god) by Mādayya, the son of Śankarayya and the grand son of Madanayya of Terakaṇāmbi.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1686 and Kali 4865, Svabhānu, Jyeshṭha, śu. 5. The cyclic year Svabhānu occurred in Śaka 1685 while in 1686 the next cyclic year Taraṇa occured.</p>						

						</summary>
